The sandwiches are consistently good. However this restaurant is the worst. The biggest problem is the ventilation system. within two seconds your eyes are burning because they can't seem to figure out how to vent the ovens out of the building. if you can get the table up by the front door you can get a little fresh air every time someone walks in or out. But overall the smoke from the oven is pretty unbearable  today I had the displeasure of listening to an employee argue with a phone customer for a solid half hour about her DealDash order. Dessert or Shake could be the promo. Expect a line. But, it moves. The challenge is seating. Yep, you have to wait for someone to get up, and their not moving anytime soon. The order arrived before their stated timeframe, the delivery guy was nice, the chili was very good and included a pack of oyster crackers, and they even made a substitution for the blue cheese on my salad.  Overall, the Uptown salad was good, except that they didn't include the chicken and the apples were so mushy I had to pick them out.  I double checked my order history and saw that I did order the salad that cost more and listed chicken as being included (the cheaper salad specifically said "no chicken"), so I'm not sure what happened.  It was only $1 more for the salad with the chicken, but I was still a bit disappointed.  I will likely order from Potbelly again, but I will make a note about the chicken so it's not forgotten next time.

I must disagree with the other two reviews. I think Potbelly is definitely a step up from Subway. I have a pretty mature and discerning palette and was pretty impressed by the grilled chicken and cheddar sandwich I had on whole grain bread. Granted it was lunch time, and I was hungry, but I ate every crumb. I'm not saying its the healthiest pace to eat, but it is DEFINITELY tastier than Subway. I went with three friends, two of them got salads. They commented that they were okay, but not really tossed, and after putting all the toppings on it, you might as well get a sandwich. The line was long but moved quickly and they are very lax when it comes to substitutions on the fly. I will  definitely be returning for lunch soon.
